<refnamediv><refname>imresize3</refname><refpurpose>Resize a 3D image volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imresize3(volume, outputSize)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Input 3-D volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>outputSize</term><listitem><para>Three-element output size <literal>[rows cols slices]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Resized 3-D volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Resizes a three-dimensional volume using nearest-neighbor sampling and [rows cols slices] output dimensions.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_smarties.png"));
gray = rgb2gray(image);
slice2 = imtranslate(gray, [3 0]);
slice3 = imtranslate(gray, [6 0]);
volume = cat(3, gray, slice2, slice3);
small = imresize3(volume, [60 80 2]);
imshow3d(small, 1);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
